{
  "texts": [
    "Because the content of finger language is limited and belongs to static image recognition, the background environment is relatively controllable.",
    "Thus, the recognition accuracy is high, almost exceeding 90%.",
    "Additionally, CNN, 3DCNN, RNN, variants (such as LSTM, GRU, etc.",
    "), and Transformer models, are more suitable for continuous sign language recognition.",
    "Due to the temporal dynamics and contextual information involved in continuous sign languages, the relative recognition accuracy is lower and more challenging."
  ]
}